---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About - Paul's Second Brain" description="About Paul and this digital garden">
  <div class="about">
    <h1>About</h1>

    <section class="about-section">
      <h2>This Digital Garden</h2>
      <p>
        This is my second brainâ€”a place to externalize thoughts, ideas, and learnings.
        It's built on the Zettelkasten method, a note-taking system that emphasizes
        connections between ideas rather than hierarchical organization.
      </p>
      <p>
        The content here is a living, breathing collection. Notes evolve, connections
        form, and ideas mature over time. Some notes are polished essays, others are
        raw explorations. That's the nature of a digital garden.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="about-section">
      <h2>The System</h2>
      <p>
        I organize my notes into three main categories:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Reference Notes:</strong> Highlights and excerpts from articles, books,
          and other sources I've consumed.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Literature Notes:</strong> Ideas from references explained in my own words,
          showing I've processed and understood the concepts.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Permanent Notes:</strong> Original thoughts and connections between ideas,
          the synthesis that emerges from engaging with the material.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="about-section">
      <h2>The Stack</h2>
      <p>
        This site is built with Astro, a modern static site generator that ships
        zero JavaScript by default. The content lives in markdown files that I edit
        with Obsidian, my note-taking tool of choice.
      </p>
      <p>
        The design emphasizes readability with a muted color palette, generous
        whitespace, and typography optimized for long-form reading.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="about-section">
      <h2>Get in Touch</h2>
      <p>
        If you'd like to connect, discuss ideas, or share feedback about this site,
        feel free to reach out.
      </p>
      <div class="links">
        <a href="https://github.com/paulliwali" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about {
    max-width: 680px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .about h1 {
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-xl);
  }

  .about-section {
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-xl);
    padding-bottom: var(--spacing-xl);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .about-section:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .about-section h2 {
    color: var(--color-accent-sage);
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .about-section p {
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
  }

  .about-section ul {
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
  }

  .about-section li {
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-sm);
  }

  .links {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--spacing-md);
    margin-top: var(--spacing-md);
  }

  .links a {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-weight: 600;
    padding: var(--spacing-sm) var(--spacing-md);
    background-color: var(--color-bg-secondary);
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    transition: all 0.2s ease;
  }

  .links a:hover {
    background-color: var(--color-accent-sage);
    color: white;
    border-color: var(--color-accent-sage);
  }
</style>
